OL,5, A woman has pulled out of running the  
OL,6, New York City Marathon after organisers
OL,7, said she could not wear a vest carrying
OL,8, supplies for her stoma and water.      
OL,10,FGayle Redmon, a GP from Flint,         
OL,11,FFlintshire, said the vest had allowed  
OL,12,Fher to safely run marathons in London  
OL,13,Fand Paris.                             
OL,15,FShe said she believed she had been     
OL,16,Fdiscriminated against.                 
OL,18,FNew York Road Runners (NYRR), which    
OL,19,Forganises the race, said the vest did  
OL,20,Fnot adhere to rules set by police.     
